  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Support to Crisis-Affected Afghan Nationals in Pakistan, Iran and Tajikistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of this project is to support Afghan nationals outside of Afghanistan and their host communities, to respond to their immediate humanitarian needs and work towards durable solutions for those who are displaced in Iran, Pakistan and Tajikistan. In line with IOM&#x2019;s Comprehensive Action Plan for Afghanistan and Neighboring Countries, this project aims to support Afghan populations, including new arrivals whilst also working with government institutions and host communities to mitigate the short to medium term impacts of the crisis on societies and contribute to recovery and resilience for longer-term sustainable development.</narrative>
  </description>
